    "Wang Ning is the founder, chairman and CEO of Pop Mart International Group, a toy company that went public in Hong Kong in 2020.",
    "Set up in 2010, Pop Mart sells small figurines for about $10 each in so-called blind boxes that don't reveal the toys inside.",
    "The company partners with artists to come up with different lines of toys. Its best-selling series include Dimoo, Molly and Skullpanda.",
    "Pop Mart also sells to overseas markets such as Europe, Southeast Asia and the U.S."
